   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>Actually, my thought was that the folder structure would reflect the inheritance.

So you'd have mysite/templates/base.html (and a few similarly oft-inherited
templates like one-column in there), then mysite/templates/missions/base.html,
then mysite/templates/missions/svn_mission/base.html, etc.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
  <tr>
   <th><a href="msg1185">msg1185 (view)</a></th>
   <th>Author: paulproteus</th>
   <th>Date: 2011-02-26.22:07:39</th>
   <th>
    
   </th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>If you look for "base/base.html" it's in "base/templates/base/base.html". Why
all the repetition?

Answer: Django apps.

We could just move all the OpenHatch templates into one big templates directory
instead. Like
* mysite/templates/base/base.html
* mysite/templates/missions/svn_mission/base.html

rather than

* mysite/base/templates/base/base.html
* mysite/missions/templates/missions/svn_mission/base.html

That would probably make things nicer.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
